{
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "<p>\n    Umiejętność rozwiązywania równań wielomianowych przydaje się w niektórych zadaniach tekstowych. Przyjrzyjmy się dwóm przykładom.\n</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "<p class=\"question\">\n</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "\n        Iloczyn trzech kolejnych liczb całkowitych jest równy \\(2\\,730\\).\n        <p>\n            Znajdź te liczby.\n        </p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "spoiler",
      "label": "rozwiązanie",
      "body": "\n\n<div class=\"ks_tabs\" id=\"tabs-1\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a class=\"chosen\" href=\"#tabcontent-1-1\" id=\"tab-1-1\">\n                        nagranie\n                    </a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"#tabcontent-1-2\" id=\"tab-1-2\">\n                        krok po kroku\n                    </a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"visible\" id=\"tabcontent-1-1\">\n<h3>\n                    Równanie wielomianowe\n                </h3>\n<figure>\n<video controls=\"\" width=\"100%\">\n<source src=\"static/rownanie_wielomianowe_zad_1_rownanie.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n</video>\n</figure>\n<h3>\n                    Pierwszy pierwiastek\n                </h3>\n<figure>\n<video controls=\"\" width=\"100%\">\n<source src=\"static/rownanie_wielomianowe_zad_1_pierwiastek.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n</video>\n</figure>\n<h3>\n                    Rozwiązanie\n                </h3>\n<figure>\n<video controls=\"\" width=\"100%\">\n<source src=\"static/rownanie_wielomianowe_zad_1_rozwiazanie.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n</video>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<div id=\"tabcontent-1-2\">\n<div class=\"switch_steps\">\n<div class=\"switch_step\">\n                        Niech \\(x\\) oznacza pierwszą z trzech liczb całkowitych.\n                        <div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            Wówczas kolejne dwie liczby to\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(x+1\\) i \\(x+2\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(2x\\) i \\(3x\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(2x+1\\) i \\(3x+2\\)\n                            </div>\n                            .\n                            <div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<p>\n                            Ich iloczyn jest równy \\(2\\,730\\), więc \\(x(x+1)(x+2)=2\\,730\\).\n                        </p>\n<p>\n                            Teraz wymnóż nawiasy i przenieś wszystkie wyrazy na lewą stronę.\n                        </p>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            Otrzymujemy równanie\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(x^3+3x^2+2x+2\\,730=0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(x^3+3x^2+2x-2\\,730=0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(x^3+2x^2+3x+2\\,730=0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(x^3+2x^2+3x-2\\,730=0\\)\n                            </div>\n                            .\n                            <div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<p>\n                            Wypiszmy dzielniki wyrazu wolnego parami - aby iloczyn dzielników w każdej parze był równy \\(2\\,730\\). (Uzupełnij brakujące dzielniki.)\n                        </p>\n<div id=\"question482\">\n<div class=\"centered\">\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_border\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                                \\(1\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(2\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n<input class=\"table_input\" placeholder=\"?\" style=\"width: 40px;\" type=\"text\"/>\n</td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(5\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(6\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(7\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(10\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(13\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(15\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n<input class=\"table_input\" placeholder=\"?\" style=\"width: 40px;\" type=\"text\"/>\n</td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(26\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(30\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(35\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(39\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(42\\)\n                                            </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                                \\(2\\,730\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(1\\,365\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(910\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(546\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(455\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(390\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n<input class=\"table_input\" placeholder=\"?\" style=\"width: 40px;\" type=\"text\"/>\n</td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(210\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(182\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(130\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(105\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(91\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(78\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(70\\)\n                                            </td>\n<td>\n                                                \\(65\\)\n                                            </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"hidden\" id=\"success_question482\">\n<p>\n                                Sporo podejrzanych! Ułatwię Ci trochę zadanie.\n                            </p>\n<p>\n                                Przyjmijmy:\n                            </p>\n                            \\[\n                            W(x)=x^3+3x^2+2x-2\\,730\n                            \\]\n                            <p>\n                                i sprawdźmy:\n                            </p>\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder\">\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n                                            \\[\n                                            \\begin{align*}\n                                            W(1)&amp;=1^3+3\\cdot 1^2+2\\cdot 1-2\\,730=-2\\,724\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(-1)&amp;=(-1)^3+3\\cdot (-1)^2+2\\cdot (-1)-2\\,730=-2\\,730\\ne 0\n                                            \\end{align*}\n                                            \\]\n                                            i dalej:\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                            \\[\n                                            W(2)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(3)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(5)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(6)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(7)\\ne 0\n                                            \\]\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\[\n                                            W(-2)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(-3)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(-5)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(-6)\\ne 0\\\\\n                                            W(-7)\\ne 0\n                                            \\]\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>\n                                Teraz pora na Ciebie.\n                            </p>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                                \\(W(10)=10^3+3\\cdot 10^2+2\\cdot 10-2\\,730=\\)\n                                <br/>\n                                \\(=1\\,000+300+20-2\\,730\\)\n                                <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                    &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                                </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                    \\(=0\\)\n                                </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                    \\(\\ne 0\\)\n                                </div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                    zatwierdź\n                                </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            \\(W(-10)=(-10)^3+3\\cdot (-10)^2+2\\cdot (-10)-2\\,730=\\)\n                            <br/>\n                            \\(=-1\\,000+300-20-2\\,730\\)\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(=0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(\\ne 0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            \\(W(13)=13^3+3\\cdot 13^2+2\\cdot 13-2\\,730=\\)\n                            <br/>\n                            \\(=2\\,197+507+26-2\\,730\\)\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(=0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(\\ne 0\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n<p>\n                            Skoro \\(x=13\\) jest pierwiastkiem wielomianu \\(W(x)\\), to możemy podzielić ten wielomian przez \\((x-13)\\).\n                        </p>\n                        Wykonaj dzielenie i jeśli chcesz\n                        <details>\n<summary>\n                                sprawdź wynik.\n                            </summary>\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder\">\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                                            \\(x^{2}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(+16x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(+210\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                            \\((x^{3}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(+3x^{2}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(+2x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-2730)\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(:(x-13)\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                                            \\(x^{3}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-13x^{2}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                            \\(=\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(16x^{2}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(+2x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-2730\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(16x^{2}\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-208x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(=\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(210x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-2730\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(210x\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(-2730\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(=\\)\n                                        </td>\n<td>\n                                            \\(\\)\n                                        </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</details>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            Wynikiem dzielenia jest\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\((x^2+16x+210)\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\((x^2-16x+210)\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\((x^2+16x-210)\\)\n                            </div>\n                            .\n                            <div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n                        Mamy jedno rozwiązanie równania, a skoro rozłożyliśmy je do postaci\n                        \\[\n                        (x-13)(x^2+16x+210)=0\n                        \\]\n                        powinniśmy jeszcze sprawdzić, czy są jakieś rozwiązania wynikające z czynnika kwadratowego.\n                        <br/>\n                        W tym celu obliczymy\n                        <strong>\n                            deltę\n                        </strong>\n                        - wyróżnik równania kwadratowego.\n                        <details>\n<summary>\n                                delta - przypomnienie\n                            </summary>\n<div class=\"important\">\n                                Dla równania kwadratowego\n                                \\[\n                                Ax^2+Bx+C=0\n                                \\]\n                                <small>\n                                    (w którym zmienną jest \\(x\\))\n                                </small>\n                                wyróżnik tego równania (zwany\n                                <strong>\n                                    deltą\n                                </strong>\n                                ) obliczamy według wzoru:\n                                \\[\n                                \\Delta=B^2-4AC\n                                \\]\n                            </div>\n</details>\n<div class=\"switch_line\">\n                            Dla równania \\(x^2+16x+210=0\\) otrzymujemy \\(\\Delta=\\)\n                            <div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                &gt;&gt; wybierz &gt;&gt;\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(584\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(-584\\)\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"switch_value\">\n                                \\(46\\)\n                            </div>\n                            .\n                            <div class=\"switch_show_next ks_button\">\n                                zatwierdź\n                            </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"switch_step hidden\">\n                        Ujemna delta oznacza, że jedynym rozwiązaniem równania wielomianowego jest \\(x=13\\), a to z kolei oznacza, że szukane liczby to \\(13\\), \\(14\\) i \\(15\\).\n                    </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
    },
